metadata.description: Dust-bowl Kansas, 1939. They say there's no place like home, but after seeing the wonders of Oz, Dorothy Gale is finding it hard adjusting to a "normal" life back on Earth. So when dust storms, circus freaks, and flying monkeys descend upon her home in 1930s Kansas, what's a simple (highborn) farm girl and her giant wolf to do? New allies and old friends return in this bridge tale of Oz!
metadata.name: OZ: No Place Like Home
